com.intel.fightclub.dialog

Class DialogManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intel.fightclub.dialog.DialogManager

  • public final class DialogManager
extends java.lang.Object
    Main entry point to interact with the Dialog libraries. This class wraps Tts, Asr and Nlu in a singleton implementation. All components are lazily initialized, only being created whenever getInstance is called for the first time.

      • addCUIListener

        @NonNull
public Registration addCUIListener(@NonNull
                                            CUIListener dialogListener)

        Adds a CUIListener instance which will receive events from ASR, TTS, and dialog engines. Any callbacks will be run on the thread used to add this listener.

        This will also initialize the ASR, TTS, and dialog components if the listener that is added is the only one in the set.

        Parameters:
        dialogListener - an implementation of Dialog Listener to listen on ASR/TTS events.
        Returns:
        Registration token which can be used to unregister the listener.

      • triggerLpalMode

        @CheckResult
public boolean triggerLpalMode()
        Forces the dialog to go into low power, always listening (LPAL) mode. In this mode, only the phrase "Hey, Coach!" will be recognized by the speech recognition engine. Once this trigger phrase is recognized, the dialog will switch back to a normal operation mode.
        Returns:
        True if the operation has been successfully enqueued on the handler. This does not indicate that dialog has transitioned into LPAL mode.

      • startWorkout

        public void startWorkout(@NonNull
                         WorkoutParameters workoutParameters)
        Offers CUI actions the possibility to start the workout. This method will pass this message onto the DialogManager's thread. The DM's thread will then invoke this specific action on the Mediator. The rationale behind this is that CUI actions need a thread to execute their async behavior in. The DM will be able to tell the Mediator to start the workout and will listen to any success/failure events related to this call.
        Parameters:
        workoutParameters - The parameters for the workout that will be started.

      • stopWorkout

        public void stopWorkout()
        Offers CUI actions the possibility to stop the workout. This method will pass this message onto the DialogManager's thread. The DM's thread will then invoke this specific action on the Mediator. The rationale behind this is that CUI actions need a thread to execute their async behavior in. The DM will be able to tell the Mediator to stop the workout and will listen to any success/failure events related to this call.

      • cancelWorkout

        public void cancelWorkout()
        Offers CUI actions the possibility to cancel the workout. This method will pass this message onto the DialogManager's thread. The DM's thread will then invoke this specific action on the Mediator. The rationale behind this is that CUI actions need a thread to execute their async behavior in. The DM will be able to tell the Mediator to cancel the workout and will listen to any success/failure events related to this call.

      • generateApplicationInfo

        @NonNull
public AppInfoBundle generateApplicationInfo()
        Generates a bundle containing information about the application and modules. This is mostly meant to generate a comprehensive summary of all modules and components currently integrated in the application, to be persisted by the CUI in the logs it generates. This method is designed for internal use of the DialogManager, but has been made public to enable the UI to get the same summary and display it on a debug screen.
        Returns:
        Information about the application as well as modules currently being utilized in the CUI.
